text:
Did anyone told you that School was literally USELESS? Team fearless, I know that we have to live our life, I know that we have to truely live every second. But, school is just here to waste your time, You can't get out because you have homeworks, you have to waste a whole year because you have official exams to pass, you have to waste 7 hours a day learning things that will NEVER help you in this life! b^2-4ac, IN WHAT THIS FORMULA HERE WILL HELP ME IN MY FUTURE?! How can I live life if Parents won't let you get out of house because "you have to study". I'VE SPENT 16 YEARS TO SCHOOL AND WHAT DID I HAVE?! What? Answer this question here, what did I have..? A diploma? A diploma.. Heh.. This is laughable, tell me why most of the successful people YOU HAVE MENTIONNED in this video, are dropouts, why only dropouts are successful, oh wait a second, because they knew that they had to get out of that road, what kind of road? That road where everyone is walking on, EVERYONE!!! We are living a LIE god damn it!!! That road tells us to: Go to school, go to the university, find a job that you DO NOT like just for MONEY and WORK FOR SOMEBODY (you'll be an employee in most of the cases), have a familly, and die. Is that life? Is that life?! NO AND NO this is a life of someone who is living a LIE, for the familly, in most of the cases, THERE IS PROBLEMS, THERE IS PROBLEMS, why only few people are living happily with their familly and the rest are having problems? Why..? Because they do not understand? No, because they haven't be taught how to be happy, they haven't be taught how to choose your partner, they haven't been taught all of this.. What they have been taught you say? They have been taught how to do maths, they have been taught that "having problems in a relation ship is normal", they have been taught to do anything for money, and not for themselves, they have been taught BULLSHIT! 

I have a goal in life, but too bad I have to wait until I pass those exams I have, to be free. 
That goal, is to awake people, to tell them that they are living a lie, that they have to be themselves but not to be who they think they are, I have to tell them that if they truely love themselves, they would work on themselves: If you were obese, you would work on yourself because you truely love yourself and you don't want to die because of obesity (that's an example), if you want to have Randy Orton's body, you would WORK to have it, you would GO to the gym! I personally do go to the gym, it's been 3 weeks now, thank god my parents agreed and didn't told me to stay at home because I have exams to pass or homeworks to do. Now, how would I make this happen? How can I achieve my goal? I have a plan, I already have a plan, guys, I'm 17 years old and I clearly know what to do in life, and how to do it, I want to be a movie producer and make movies about those lies we're living  I want to make interviews, I want to talk about that on TV, on the media, SHARE IT EVERYWHERE!!! I do make montage, I do graphic designs on Blender, I want to share it at any cost. 

As for love, I'm not going to search for it, no. I'm instead going to wait, until I find that this person fits with me, love isn't only by "seeing" someone, or "looking" at someone, love comes after friendship, you have to live things with that friend, you have to know how this person thinks, now, of course, not everyone can have the same thought, if you were about to argue to see who the heck is right about something, it means that you don't love the person that is right in front of you, because, who cares about who is right or who is wrong? Now there's limits, of course (am I getting off topic lmao?) if you love someone that says: killing is good, you should do something, of course (I'll just ask how you could love someone that loves killing lol, but idc love is love üòâ).

Just wanted to point that out.. School is useless, it teaches you: you failed a test, you're a failure. It does not teaches you: You failed a test, you will do better next time. Nah hell no they aren't teaching you that (now there's billions of school out there, and I'm sure there's great ones that has a good system, like FINLAND school system or Khan Akademy).

"I'll not say that life isn't fair, because we haven't truely living it yet"- S Shadow. 

There, I made a quote. :)Ôªø

text:
wow, don't you just LOVE when someone encases people in a category? It's like they think they know more about you than yourself. Let's debunk every part of this incredibly ignorant comment so this self-entitled person actually tries and inform themselves (maybe YOU need to spend a little more time on the internet doing some actual reading), hold on tight cause it's a long one:

1. Millennails are lazt af.
Oh really, funny how millennials show A LOT HIGHER graduation rates from high school, and even more college enrollment than non-millennial generations. I don't know what your definition of lazy is, but in my world working hard to be a professional in something is the opposite of being lazy. Sorry we aren't a bunch of dropouts who decided living a mediocre life was enough (yeah I'm talking to you "millennials lack purpose" guy). I'm just shoving these facts here since you didn't really say why are we lazy exactly. Is it cause we spend time on the internet? honey, we were born in a technological era, thanks to technology we actually do have more dreams and high goals,  besides, didn't yall spend all your time listening to the radio or watching tv all day? 

2. That last point in 1 actually brings me to this one, what exactly do you call being in "reality" lmfao. Last time I checked we millennials have to deal with the fucking mess your generations made. It so much more expensive to live, to buy a house, to be economically stable.. etc. We spend time on the  internet because times have evolved, should we just sit on our asses all day playing yaxes then? And actually, news and information are SO accessible and fast-traveling thanks to the internet, we GET a picture of reality, trust me, we just don't have to wait a week till it's printed on a newspaper.  We end up making wrong decisions? is that a millennial thing really? here was I thinking that that's how a human learns and gains experience. (btw didn't your generations feel the need to spend millions on armies and guns instead of focusing on education, health and stability?)

3. "Knowing reality" is something a human being in this society learns from experience, times have changed and yeah we didn't grow up like you did, that doesn't mean we lack sensibility, actually, I think millennials are the most hopeful,  humanitarian and socially aware generation thanks to the atrocities your generation did, thank you for showing us how it ISN'T done. The struggles we encounter as adults are not because we're lazy, it's cause of the world that was inherited to us and the systems that were taught to us that are obsolete and failed to adapt to a fast developing society, the education system is a perfect example, are you really blaming us for being shoved into these systems that don't fit us anymore? 

They say that knowledge is freedom, the more you learn, the  better version of yourself you are, so  yes, it is about books and not just books, but videos, blogs, articles, etc that are available to us with a click.

P.S I'm aware past generations did inherit us all these tools we can develop ourselves with, I'm just stating that ya'll created these tools and for some reason don't expect us to use them or adapt to them. We millennials are hopeful and full of creativity, you know what really gets in our way? idiots encasing us in a box with set characteristics because they are too narrow minded to actually inform themselves, you know, like the ones who think they know about you more than you know about yourself.Ôªø

author: duranni hilmi

text: As much as I agree with this video's motives, sometimes you need to relax, you NEED to "waste" time or you will burn out. You say that you need to do things you enjoy, but imply that playing video games or spending time with friends is a waste? Surely if you enjoy something, you are filling your life with more happy memories. If your goal is only to work more, then will you ever reach your goal? Surely a life spent with no relaxation or time just to breathe is more of a waste than one with less stress and happiness. Yes you need to work hard, but you need to play hard too, this balance is importance. It seems as if work or leisure are two separate things, but can't we have both? Although you say each second you "waste" could be used to gain knowledge to make you more successful, you could have also spent those few seconds appreciating the world around you, the people around you, the family around you. After all, a clear mind has more room to understand new things than one already crumbling under stress. No matter how knowledgable or "successful" you are, in the end we are all people and once our lives are over, they are equally over. I for one fall as a victim to over stress about work and have lost many opportunities in life because of it. Yes, without work we do not get rewards, but we need to spend time appreciating the rewards life has giving us too.Ôªø

text:
Am I the only person who thinks that wasting time is also ok? that partying with your friends is also ok? That enjoying your life in whatever you want to is also ok? This video tells you not to give up on your dreams because then you are failing but sometimes people change and the dreams they had in the past are no longer so important for them.

This video just reminds me of many people obsessed with success, that never hang out with their friends, that have very low social skills, that are terrified of failure only looking for a better life in the future and are not happy at all.

I agree that learning is important, that reading is great for your mind and your life (I LOVE reading), but the message this video sends is different.Ôªø

text: Some of the things they said are true. But the fact that they think playing video games and partying is bad and reading books is good suprises me. This is a motivational video, not "Every parent ever". I mean I get it that most of the people use video games as a drug of some kind and yes those people need to get their shit together and start being productive but there are some people that are happy with their life spent on video games and in clubs. If you tell them that the only way of spending time usefully is by reading books, then they will believe that they are usefull only when they read and some day they are gonna realise that they never accomplished their dreams, instead they spent their life doing "the right thing". What I suggest and personally do is: every day spend an hour or so doing what you really want to. The rest of the day you can do what society wants you too (read books, study, be smart, be productive and all that shit). text:
Okay, so is becoming the best version of yourself means being famous, being rich, and being successful? Is this what this video is giving the message? Is this what the real definition of being the "Best Version Of Yourself" is meaning having to accomplish all of these things in life? Because somehow I find this video a little contradicted? I mean, I truly understand the whole "never stop learning part in life" and "reading books" and "never give up to chase your dreams" but the moment he says that the "The success is not about the money, the fame or the big house. It's in fact about becoming the "Best Version of Yourself... now, you see this is the part where I get distracted the most when the speaker emphasizes so much on being "The Richest Man" and "how the Richest Man Bill Gates was once asked a question and The Richest Man Replied and many more times... repeating the same thing and yet trying to give the message that to be the "Best Verison of Yourself."... is not about any of these things? I mean...

Well, my only question is that can one not become the best version of himself without being rich, famous, and successful, unlike Bill, Warren, and Opera, they are all rich?  No wonder that they are all nice people but I DO know for sure that they are so many richest people on this planet and they are definitely¬†NOT the best version kind of people... 

I truly find that the title of this video should not be what it is...just wanted to say what I felt that's all...  

To me, what I believe that becoming the "Best Version of Yourself" is entirely a whole different thing...It's all about who and what you are from the INSIDE, and not the OUTSIDE and certainly not having all the money in the world...Ôªø
author: Gaurav Gautam
